  <h3 style="color: var(--dark-blue); font-size: 17px; margin-top: 24px;">The Explorer</h3>
  <p>The three panels below let you explore how Z-scores, raw values, and tail areas relate to the actual childcare pilot data. The <strong>full-sample panel</strong> sits at the top: it tests the empirical rule against the actual data by showing the symmetric band around the mean and comparing the model's predicted count with the count observed in the data. The <strong>two subgroup panels</strong> below split the same 500 employees by work schedule and use a one-sided cutoff to show how the same Z-score corresponds to different raw values across the two subgroups.</p>
  
  <div class="explorer-section">
    <!-- FULL SAMPLE PANEL: empirical rule (symmetric band) -->
    <div class="panel full-sample" data-panel="full">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <div class="title">Full childcare pilot sample (empirical rule mode)</div>
        <div class="stats">Mean = 6.53 days · SD = 3.66 · n = 500</div>
